{"title_page": "Crimean Federal University", "text_new": "{{merge to|Tavrida National V.I. Vernadsky University|discuss=Talk:Tavrida National V.I. Vernadsky University#Proposed merge with V.I. Vernadsky Crimean Federal University|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name = V.I. Vernadsky Crimean Federal University\n|native_name = \u041a\u0440\u044b\u043c\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0444\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0443\u043d\u0438\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0441\u0438\u0442\u0435\u0442 \u0438\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0412.\u0418. \u0412\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0430\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e\n|image_name = \n|image_size = 200px\n|motto = ''Nosce te ipsum'' ([[Latin]])\n|mottoeng = Know thyself\n|established = 1918\n|type = [[Federal university]]\n|rector = Andrei Falaleev\n|president = \n|students = 35000\n|academic_staff = \n|campus = \n|colours = \n|address = 4, Academica Vernanskogo Avenue\n|city = [[Simferopol]], [[Crimea]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|44|56|11|N|34|08|03|E|region:UA-43_type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n|country = [[Russia]]/[[Ukraine]]\n|website = http://www.eng.cfuv.ru\n{{Infobox building\n| embed = yes\n| name               = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| image              = \t\u0422\u041d\u0423 - panoramio (4).jpg\n| image_size         = 250px\n| caption            = \n| start_date         = \n| completion_date    = \n| location           =\n| coordinates        =             \n| map_type           = \n| architectural      = \n| status             = \n| antenna_spire      = \n| top_floor          = \n| floor_count        = \n| elevator_count     = \n| floor_area         = \n| developer          = \n| owner              = \n}}\n}}\n'''V.I. Vernadsky Crimean Federal University''' is a higher education institution located in [[Simferopol]] and created in 2014, on the basis of [[Tavrida National V.I. Vernadsky University]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tass.com/russia/727189|title=New federal university to be created in Crimea|website=TASS|language=ru|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref> It has a century-long history with a network of research and production facilities, which has more than 7,000 staff and over 32,000 students, including about 3,000 international students from 54 countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crfu.ru/about-university/|title=About university|website=Crimean Federal University|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tass.com/russia/724261|title=Russia plans to set up a federal university in Crimea|website=TASS|language=ru|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref>\n\nThe university was named after the academician [[Vladimir Vernadsky]].\n\n== History ==\nThe university began its history from the Decree of the Crimean Territorial Government September 3, 1918 \"On the Establishment of the Taurida University\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tnu.edu.ua/index.php/en/history|title=History Taurida of University|last=|first=|date=|website=tnu.edu.ua|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n\nDuring the development of Crimea as a health resort, it was decided in 1930 to organize higher medical school here.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.studyeurope.in/mbbs-in-russia/crimea-federal-university/|title=Crimea Federal University, Russia Fees and Admission Process|website=Study Europe Consultants.|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref> The opening of the Crimean Medical Institute took place on 1 April 1931.\n\nThe 100th anniversary of the  Crimean Federal University October 14, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.kremlin.ru/events/president/news/58826|title=Greetings on 100th anniversary of Vernadsky Crimean Federal University|website=President of\u00a0Russia|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indrastra.com/2019/03/Putin-Visit-to-Crimea-5th-Anniversary-Accession-005-03-2019-0045.html|title=Putin Visiting Crimea to Celebrate Crimean Accession to Russia|website=www.indrastra.com|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n\nThe development of new campuses of the Crimean Federal University began in August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.c-inform.info/comments/id/375|title=\u041a\u0424\u0423 \u0441\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u0435\u0442 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u0446\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0440\u044b \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0442\u044f\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u0434\u043b\u044f \u043a\u0440\u044b\u043c\u0447\u0430\u043d|website=www.c-inform.info|access-date=2019-08-25}}</ref>\n\n== Parks ==\n[[File:The TNU Botanical Garden in Simferopol, Crimea, Ukraine 18.JPG|thumb|right|\nPlace of leisure in University Park]]\n[[File:The TNU Botanical Garden in Simferopol, Crimea, Ukraine 01.JPG|thumb|right|\nIt's Spring in the Botanic Garden]]\nThe university parks are 103,78-acre (42 he) parkland area in the south of the city, near [[Tavrida National V.I. Vernadsky University|Taurida Academy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wikimapia.org/14883901/Salhirka-Park-Botanical-Gardens|title=Salhirka Park, Botanical Gardens - Simferopol|website=wikimapia.org|access-date=2019-05-01}}</ref> The park is open to the public during daylight hours.\n\n[[Vorontsov house]] is located in the park university. The house residence [[Mikhail Semyonovich Vorontsov|Mikhail Vorontsov]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FCNv8i3p8ekC&pg=PA118&lpg=PA118&dq=Vorontsov+house+in+simferopol&source=bl&ots=IO1yD2j7y3&sig=ACfU3U18NzbD28ZteVjbRuSy7NTBGUY-Dw&hl=ru&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj3vtSc6_rhAhVqk4sKHT_RA504FBDoATACegQICRAB#v=onepage&q=Vorontsov%20house%20in%20simferopol&f=false|title=Prince Michael Vorontsov: Viceroy to the Tsar|last=Rhinelander|first=Anthony L. H.|date=July 1990|publisher=McGill-Queen's Press - MQUP|isbn=9780773507470}}</ref>\n\nOn the territory of the Botanic garden and in the campus of the [[Tavrida National V.I. Vernadsky University|Taurida Academy]] is a library of science.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rg.ru/2017/12/21/reg-ufo/biblioteka-kfu-stala-intellektualno-informacionnym-centrom-kryma.html|title=\u